<HEADLINE> 22 Killed in Escalated Violence in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a major encounter, a "Pakistani militant" identified as Noor-
ud-din and three security personnel were killed at a village in
Jammu region on Wednesday night, the PTI quoted an official
spokesman in Srinagar, capital of Jammu and Kashmir state, as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Four local militants were killed in two separate encounters
with security forces in Pulwama districts of south Kashmir on
Thursday, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, six militants were arrested along with some arms and
ammunition in Jammu and Kashmir on Thursday, he noted. 
</P>
