<HEADLINE> Sensex Continues to Rise on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index closed at 4,728.81 as against
Wednesday's close of 4,604.84, netting a sharp gain of 123.97
points or 2.69 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index rose by 52.13 points to 2,333.87 from
previous close of 2,281.74.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted remarkably up at
502.36 and 186.78 compared with previous close of 491.39 and 183.
06, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index also improved up by 32.49 points to 1,524.78
from Wednesday's close of 1,492.29. 
</P>
