<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manpower Export, Remittances from Expatriates Increase in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Manpower export and remittances from
the expatriate Bangladeshis increased over 11 percent in the last
fiscal year and showed a positive impact on the economy.
</P>
<P>
According to Economic Survey Report 2000 released in parliament
Thursday, in 1998-99, over 270 thousands of Bangladeshi citizens
went abroad with jobs.
</P>
<P>
The increase in manpower export was 11.11 percent over the
previous year, the report said, adding that the amount of money
sent by the expatriates was 1.7 billion U.S. dollars in 1998-99,
an 11.82 percent increase compared to the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Qualitative changes in the exported manpower of Bangladesh are
also remarkable. The number of skilled manpower export is
increasing day by day.
</P>
<P>
A good number of laborers are going to the Middle East
countries every year and most of them to Saudi Arabia and Kuwait.
Besides the Middle East, the Bangladeshi laborers are also going
to Malaysia, Singapore Brunei, Mauritius and Cyprus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
