<HEADLINE> Water Level of Tsho Rolpa Lake to be Reduced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The project of reducing the water
level of the Tsho Rolpa glacial lake, which is feared to burst out
due to global warming, began Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"There will be no danger of the lake bursting when the water
level is reduced three meters after the completion of the project,
" said Adarsha Pokherel, director general of the Department of
Hydrology and Meteorology.
</P>
<P>
The Tsho Rolpa glacier lake is located 110 kilometers northeast
of Kathmandu at an altitude of 4500 meters in Rolwaling Valley of
Dolakha district.
</P>
<P>
The area of the lake is gradually increasing and if the lake
bursts it is likely to affect 10,000 people living in the
Rolwaling valley.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government had installed flood warning sirens at 19
settlements of 17 villages in the lake area to check the loss of
lives and property from the possible outburst of the lake.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
