<HEADLINE> Gibbs Admits Accepting $15,000 for Losing Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- South African cricketer
Herschelle Gibbs on Thursday admitted that he agreed to lose his
wicket for 15,000 U.S. dollars during the fifth one-day
international between South Africa and India earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Gibbs, testifying before the King commission into alleged match-
fixing in Cape Town, said he later lied to the United Cricket
Board of South Africa about his involvement in the incident to
protect captain Hansie Cronje.
</P>
<P>
Gibbs said Cronje had approached him before the match and
suggested that he could make himself 15,000 dollars if he went out
for less than 20 runs.
</P>
<P>
This scandal has raised a hue and cry in the criket world.
</P>
