<HEADLINE> 2,000 Striking Workers Suspended in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- About 2,000 striking workers of
Lusaka City Council of Zambia have been suspended with immediate
effect after they defied an ultimatum issued on Wednesday to
report to work Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The city council workers started to call a strike last Tuesday,
 demanding 40,000 Kwacha (about 13 U.S. dollars) outstanding
arrears per month to individual employees backdated to July last
year.
</P>
<P>
The workers are also demanding their April and May salaries
this year be paid along with the arrears in full. 
</P>
</TEXT>
