<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0022 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Notes to U.S. Envoy on Violating Diplomatic Norms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government has
served a note on U.S. Ambassador Reverend Charles Stith, accusing
him of violating diplomatic norms by airing his views on Zanzibar
through the mass media instead of the acceptable diplomatic
channels.
</P>
<P>
A senior official of Tanzanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and
International Cooperation told a press conference here on Thursday
that as a foreign envoy, the U.S. ambassador has to abide by the
standing orders to deal with issues in a sovereign state.
</P>
<P>
Clarifying the union government's stand on the recent remarks
by Stith on Zanzibar, Director of Information and Research Patrick
Chokala said that mass media is not one of the channels of
communication between foreign envoys and host governments.
</P>
<P>
"We have served him with a note asking him to use the
acceptable diplomatic channels," said Ambassador Chokala without
disclosing more contents of the note and the date Stith was
served.
</P>
<P>
The Zanzibar government issued a similar statement on Tuesday
night asking foreign envoys based in Tanzania to refrain from
making statements which jeopardize the good relations with their
host governments.
</P>
<P>
The statement was apparently referring to reports by local
media quoting Stith as telling British Broadcasting Corporation
program, Focus on Africa, that he was against Zanzibar President
Salmin Amour's dictation of the next Zanzibar president.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. envoy is said to have portrayed President Amour, whose
second and last term will expire in October, as "a lame duck".
</P>
<P>
However, Stith clarified later on with the media that he was
misquoted and that he believed the decision to choose a candidate
was solely the responsibility of the political parties.
</P>
<P>
"This is totally against diplomatic norms," said the statement,
 expressing further concern over Stith's remarks that Zanzibar
could be another Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar was also displeased with Stith's violation of
diplomatic ethics by "often entering Zanzibar without informing
the Zanzibar office of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and
International Cooperation", the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar has requested foreign envoys accredited to Tanzania to
abide by diplomatic norms and refrain from intervening in
Tanzania's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The semi-autonomous Zanzibar region in the Indian Ocean joined
with mainland Tanganyika to form the United Republic of Tanzania
after a revolt in 1964 that ousted the sultan and Omani Arabs who
ruled the island.
</P>
<P>
There are four candidates from the ruling Chama Cha Mapinduzi
(CCM) party vying for Zanzibar presidency, including Zanzibar
Chief Minister Mohammed Gharib Bilala, Zanzibar Finance Minister
Amina Salum Ali, Zanzibar Communication and Transport Minister
Aman Karume, and Union Deputy Finance Minister Abdisalam Khatibu.
</P>
<P>
The CCM's National Executive Committee is scheduled to meet in
Dodoma on Saturday to scrutinize the four names by the central
committee and come up with one name.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chairman of the National Electoral Commission Judge
Lewis Makame said on Thursday that a total of 12.5 million of the
30 million population are expected to vote in 232 constituencies
throughout the country in this year's general elections on October
29.
</P>
<P>
The elections will involve the union presidential candidates,
aspirants for membership of parliament and councilorship, and the
Zanzibar presidential candidates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0023 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Air Force Launches Annual Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates' air
force has started its annual training exercises as part of a
program to keep its soldiers' combat readiness, according to a
statement released by the official WAM news agency Friday.
</P>
<P>
The one-week drilling, code named "Emirates 2000 flag," is aimed
at increasing the level of coordination between the various units
of the air force.
</P>
<P>
Symbolic air force units from the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC), which groups six Gulf Arab states -- Saudi Arabia, UAE,
Qatar, Kuwait, Bahrain and Oman -- are participating in the
exercises.
</P>
<P>
The Emirates air force has some 4,000 army personnel equipped
with 97 warplanes and 39 gunships. It has a brigade of anti-
aircraft force.
</P>
<P>
UAE leaders have reiterated that the country is building its
armed forces for the purpose of protection, not aggression.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1991 Gulf War, which ended with Iraq being driven out
of Kuwait by the U.S.-led alliance, the UAE has bought huge amounts
of weapons and military equipment, including the most advanced F-16
fighters, from the U.S., France, Britain to strengthen its forces.
</P>
<P>
It has been locked in territorial dispute with Iran, of whom the
Emirates is particularly wary, over the three islands of Abu Musa,
Greater and Lesser Tunbs, in the mouth of the strategic Strait of
Hormuz.
</P>
<P>
The GCC backs the UAE in its claim of sovereignty over the three
islands now controlled by Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Chides Israel for Delay in Carrying out Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
said on Friday that Arabs are "sick and tired" of Israel's
procrastination in implementing its agreements with the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after a meeting between Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, Moussa
expressed hope that the next few weeks will not witness more "
wasted time and unkept promises" as the Arab public opinion has
been "fed up" with Israeli procrastination.
</P>
<P>
It is now widely feared that the Palestinians will again become
victim of Israel's internal political struggle. Israeli Knesset
(parliament) on Wednesday supported in the preliminary reading an
opposition bill calling for dissolving the parliament and holding
early elections.
</P>
<P>
Asked if he thought the move was a maneuver to delay
implementation of signed agreements, Moussa said "Everything that
has happened has been intended to waste time, and serious final-
status issues such as Jerusalem, refugees, borders and settlements
have not been raised."
</P>
<P>
He called on Israel to respect commitments so that the Middle
East peace process will succeed.
</P>
<P>
Arafat wrapped up his brief visit to Egypt after the hour-long
meeting with Mubarak, during which the two leaders discussed the
Israeli foot-dragging.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinians have yet to resume talks on final-
status issues and thrash out a framework agreement, in preparation
for a permanent peace deal by September 13.
</P>
<P>
Arafat frequently visits Egypt to discuss with Mubarak ways of
pushing forward the peace process and seek advice from Mubarak, an
important peace process mediator whose country was the first Arab
country to sign a peace treaty with Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
