<HEADLINE> Russia's Putin to Visit Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin
will pay an official visit to the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea(DPRK) this Summer to "promote Russia's role in normalizing
the situation on the Korean peninsula," the Russian Foreign
Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Chairman of the DPRK Defense Commission
Kim Jong Il, President Putin "will shortly visit Pyongyang" and
this will be "our head of state's first official visit to the
country in the whole history of Russia," the ministry said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
"Moscow now wants to intensify its participation in the affairs
on the Korean peninsula, which borders on our country, towards
stabilization and the favorable development of the situation there,
"it said, stressing the relations between Moscow and Pyongyang "
have quite a long history and we have never suspended them."
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the South Korea is aware of Putin's upcoming
visit and the exact dates are being arranged.
</P>
<P>
It noted that Seoul "does not and cannot have any objections"
to the president's visit or other contacts between Russia's
representatives and the DPRK, since South Korea "knows that Russia
is for achieving stability on the peninsula."
</P>
<P>
Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov told a press conference
Friday in Moscow that a slump has been noticed in Russia's ties
with the DPRK in recent years and it should be overcome by joint
efforts.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the relationship between the two countries
will be in focus of Putin's talks with the DPRK leaders and "many
economic projects could be implemented to our mutual benefit."
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the two countries will also discuss
international problems, "mainly the situation in the Asian Pacific
region and particularly on the Korean peninsula," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last February, Ivanov visited Pyongyang and co-signed a new
treaty of friendship, good neighborliness and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that Putin also may pay a visit to Seoul because"
there is an invitation from South Korea (to Putin) and it is being
considered, but described the date of such a visit as "premature."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
