<HEADLINE> Major Cocaine Haul Seized in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Greece's economic crime police
Friday seized a total of 126 kilograms of cocaine from a Greek-
flagged vessel that arrived at the Greek port of Piraeus from
Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine, with an estimated value of 10 billion drachmas(
about 28 million U.S. dollars), was packaged in three containers
and placed among ceramic tiles, the semi-official Athens News
Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The final destination of the "Carmen" cargo is Pristina, the
capital of the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Police have arrested four suspects, including two Macedonian
citizens, one Albanian and one Greek.
</P>
<P>
It is the biggest quantity of cocaine ever discovered in
Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
