<HEADLINE> Greece Determined to Take All Measures to Combat Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Greek government Friday
expressed its determination to take all necessary measures in a
bid to fight terrorism.
</P>
<P>
During a governmental committee meeting chaired by Prime
Minister Costas Simitis, the premier called for the creation of a
united front by the government, political parties, institutions
and the people, in order to combat terrorism because the
phenomenon of terrorism distorted Greece's image, the Macedonian
Press Agency (MPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
On the possibility to change Greece's legislation on anti-
terrorism, Simitis said that no change in its core was being
discussed but an exchange of views was underway on the legal
procedure problems that might come up.
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that Greece will sign with the U.S. a
memorandum for police cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the past 25 years, Greece's November 17 terrorist group has
killed more than 20 people, including a number of U.S. diplomats
working at the U.S. embassy in Athens.
</P>
<P>
For years, the U.S. has pressured Greece to change its
domestic legislation and sign a pact for the two police forces to
closely cooperate in dealing with terrorism.
</P>
<P>
So far, Greece has passed two counter-terrorism bills and has
issued a great number of declarations as part of its efforts to
combat terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
