<HEADLINE> Singaporean PM Visits European Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Singaporean Prime
Minister Goh Chok Tong on Friday discussed with the European
Commission president how to further bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Harmonization of the electronic commerce standards was one of
the major subjects discussed between the visitor and Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
Goh told Prodi that he expected the 15-nation bloc to take
furthering bilateral relations with the European Union as one of
the challenges the union has to face.
</P>
<P>
The Singaporean prime minister said after meeting Prodi that
the EU should take steps to harmonize the standards for e-commerce
so as to increase the connectivity. The EU and Singapore are to
continue discussing the issue in October.
</P>
<P>
Prodi explained to the visitor what the EU is doing and what
can be done to develop the legal framework for better cooperation
between the EU and the Asian country.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission president described the discussion with
Goh as "wonderful" and "fruitful".
</P>
<P>
The call at the EU headquarters is the second on Goh's European
trip that took him to Germany and will take him to Ireland before
heading home. 
</P>
