<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Euro Zone Post GDP Increase in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Both the European Union and the
euro zone registered slight increase of gross domestic product (
GDP in the first quarter of this year, Eurostat reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical office of the European
Community said that the GDP grew by 0.7 percent in both the 15-
nation union and the 11-nation euro zone.
</P>
<P>
The increase followed a 0.8-percent GDP growth in the fourth
quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
The gross fixed capital formation contributed most toward the
GDP increase in both the EU and euro zone in the first three
months of the year, Eurostat said.
</P>
<P>
Exports, that grew by 3.2 percent in both the euro zone and the
EU, was another factor for the economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The first quarter of a year ago, however, witnessed a 3.2-
percent increase in the euro zone and the EU when the single
currency was launched as the credit units among 11 of the 15 EU
member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
