<HEADLINE> McRea Comes to Early Lead in Acropolis Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Colin McRae took the lead
midway though the first stage Friday in the 47th Acropolis Rally.
</P>
<P>
He came from third after the first special stage to the front
of the pack ahead of defending champion and countryman Richard
Burns.
</P>
<P>
Driving a Ford Focus WRC, McRea completed the 20.12 kilometers
third stage in 16 minutes, 23.01 seconds, 4.50 seconds, ahead of
Spain's Carlos Sainz.
</P>
<P>
The stage victory brought the 31-year-old McRae 15.7 seconds
ahead of Sainz overall and 28.90 seconds ahead of Burns in third
place.
</P>
<P>
The four-day race that covers 1,408 km through central Greece
had attracted a field of 117 drivers.
</P>
<P>
Considered one of the toughest in the world, the Acropolis
Rally counts toward the world driving championship. 
</P>
