<HEADLINE> Scientists Urged to Industrialize New Research Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
today urged scholars and scientists to accelerate technological
innovation and turn their research findings into products as soon
as possible.
</P>
<P>
These scientific achievements must be industrialized if they
are to become the driving force behind the nation's economic and
social development, Li said at the conference of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the Chinese Academy of Engineering (
CAE) which closed today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Industrialization of scientific achievements has a great
bearing on changing China's existing course of economic growth,
readjusting its economic structure and enhancing its overall
strength, he said.
</P>
<P>
Scholars of the CAS and CAE can play a very important role in
this regard, Li said.
</P>
<P>
"We must strengthen study of basic science and work to achieve
first-rate innovation results. Scholars of the two academies
should play bigger roles in basic science research," he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier called on scientists to focus on key technical
issues and make a breakthrough in the fields in which China enjoys
comparative advantages.
</P>
<P>
The scholars should train young scientists, let them advance,
pass on to them scientific methods and set an example for them in
maintaining a disciplined attitude toward academics, he said.
</P>
<P>
Popularization of scientific knowledge in all trades is crucial
for revitalizing China through science and wiping out superstition
and pseudoscience, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Scholars and scientists should regard popularization of science
as their sacred mission, write more books on popular science, and
work to improve the scientific and cultural levels of the Chinese
people, he concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
