<HEADLINE> Famous Hong Kong Company Invests in Telecom Device Manufacture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A joint venture to produce
telecommunications devices involving Hutchison Whampoa Ltd. of
Hong Kong was established today in Chongqing, the largest
municipality in west China.
</P>
<P>
The new company marks the mainland debut of the renowned
Hutchison Whampoa Ltd. in the manufacturing of telecom devices.
</P>
<P>
The Hutchison Aoputai Communication Technology Ltd. is co-
invested by Hutchison Whampoa Ltd., China Putian Information
Industry Group, and Chongqing Aoputai Communication Technology Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture has a registered capital of 57 million yuan (
6.9 million U.S. dollars), with total investment of 143 million
yuan (17 million U.S. dollars). The mainland investors hold 65
percent of the stakes.
</P>
<P>
The new company is expected to focus on fiber-optic devices for
communication, and network management systems. 
