<HEADLINE> Canada Records Lowest Jobless Rate in 24 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Canada's jobless rate was down to 6.
6 percent in May, the lowest since 1976, Statistics Canada
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The drop came after the country kept the rate at 6.8 percent
until April since last December.
</P>
<P>
Up to 38,000 full-time jobs were created in May, while 42,000
positions added to part-time employment.
</P>
<P>
Compared with May 1999, employment increased by 413,000
positions, up 2.8 percent, according to Statistics Canada.
</P>
<P>
Economists forecast an even lower jobless rate of 6 percent by
the end of the year to further reduce unemployment from 1,056,600
recorded in May. 
</P>
