<HEADLINE> River-Harnessing Project Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of a harnessing
project on the Shenzhen River, which borders south China's
Guangdong Province and Hong Kong, was finished here today after
three years of construction.
</P>
<P>
As the narrow 37-km-long river is incapable of draining flood
water during the summer flood season, the Shenzhen government
joined efforts with neighboring Hong Kong to launch the river-
harnessing project in December 1995.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the first two phases, the width of the river has
been broadened from 25 meters to 80 meters, and the river is five
meters deeper than before.
</P>
<P>
The third phase will start soon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
