<HEADLINE> Kenya to Hold Workshop on Small, Medium-sized Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government will host a
workshop on small and medium-sized enterprises in collaboration
with the Latin America Economic System (SELA) from June 12 to 15
in the country's capital Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is a result of a previous visit by SELA delegation
to Kenya in May 1999 to explore possibilities of promoting
cooperation between Latin American countries and the African
continent.
</P>
<P>
One of the major objectives of the workshop is to analyze the
achieved experiences in making industrial policies for small
enterprises, Kenyan Minister for Vocational Training Isaac Ruto
told a press conference here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"This is a critical conference for Kenya, which will boost the
country's move toward industrial transformation and poverty
eradication," Ruto noted.
</P>
<P>
The participants to this conference will come from Latin
American countries and African nations including Argentina,
Chile, Peru, South Africa and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
SELA, a regional inter-governmental organization, groups 28
Latin American and Caribbean countries with an aim to promote
economic cooperation between its member states.
</P>
<P>
The small and medium-sized enterprises employ about 61 percent
of labor force in the east African country of Kenya and
contribute to 18 percent of the country's gross domestic product,
according to the Labor and Human Resource Development Ministry.
</P>
