<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norman Beats Squillari to Reach French Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Magnus Norman reached his first Grand
Slam final when he beat unseeded Argentine Franco Squillari in
straight sets in their French Open semi-final here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The third-seeded Norman, the first Swede to reach the final at
Roland Garros since Stefan Edberg in 1989, won 6-1, 6-4, 6-3. He
has dropped only one set in the tournament so far.
</P>
<P>
He will meet either 1997 champion Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil,
the fifth seed, or 16th-seeded Spaniard Juan Carlos Ferrero in
Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
Norman, who won the Italian Open last month, beating Kuerten in
the final, will be looking to become the first Swedish champion at
Roland Garros since Mats Wilander in 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
