<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Promote Photoelectron Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Changchun Photoelectronic
Industrial Park, the first of its kind in China, was established
today in the Changchun High and New Technology Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
The park will attract home and overseas photoelectrons
producers to establish factories or branches. The products are
expected to cover laser and applied products, photoelectron
medical apparatus, photoelectron testing apparatus and optical
instruments, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
At the first phase, four development and research centers and
three enterprises will enter the park, which will cost 450 million
yuan (54 million U.S. dollars). The annual output of the park is
projected at 1.44 billion yuan (170 million U.S. dollars) at the
initial stage.
</P>
<P>
Changchun in northeast China, known as the country's automobile
city, is also the cradle of photoelectrons in China. The Changchun
Institute of Optics and Fine Mechanics and Physics under the
Chinese Academy of Sciences is China's earliest and biggest base
for research and development in photoelectrons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
