<HEADLINE> Russian State Ballet to be Held in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Ballet Theater of
Moscow will present Chaikovski's classical masterpiece Swan Lake
during its summer tour to China.
</P>
<P>
China International Youth Exchange Center and Century
Performance Corporation announced here today that the Russian
State Ballet plans to make their Beijing debut between July 14 and
16 at Century Theater.
</P>
<P>
The Russian State Ballet preserves the best traditions of the
past and demonstrates the mastery of Soviet ballet, organizers
said.
</P>
<P>
The theater is reviving the masterpieces which have made
Russian ballet so prestigious and brought it worldwide recognition,
they said.
</P>
<P>
Vyacheslav Gordeyev, artistic director of the theater, also
enjoys world fame for his choreography of three ballet pieces and
30 other dance works. 
</P>
