<HEADLINE> Iran, Kyrgyzstan Sign Agreements on Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Kyrgyzstan here on Friday
signed three cooperation agreements in the areas of diplomatic
relations, higher education and technology, and customs
administration.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi and his Kyrgyz
counterpart Iman Aliyev signed an agreement on the mutual offer of
land in Tehran and Bishkek for the future embassies and consular
offices of the two countries, the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Another agreement was signed by Iranian Minister of Science,
Research and Technology Mostafa Moin and Kyrgyz Minister of
Education and Science Beik Balatov for exchanging students at
graduate and post-graduate studies and mutual exchange of
technological know-how.
</P>
<P>
A third agreement is to facilitate customs formalities between
the two countries in the interest of better trade exchanges. It was
inked by the heads of customs administration of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The third agreement also provides for improving customs
administration of the two countries relying on computer technology
and cooperation in drug fight, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The three agreements were signed in the presence of Iranian
President Mohammad Khatami and his Kyrgyz counterpart Askar Akayev,
who arrived here Friday morning with a senior delegation for the
summit of the 10-member Economic Cooperation Organization (ECO) due
to held on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ECO was founded in 1985 by Iran, Turkey and Pakistan. The
Central Asian and Caucasian republics of Azerbaijan, Kyrgyzstan,
Turkmenistan, Tajikistan, Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan as well as
Afghanistan joined the body following the collapse of the former
Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
According to the IRNA report, President Khatami and President
Akayev also held the first round of talks ahead of the signing
ceremonies of the agreements. The two presidents reviewed current
bilateral relations and expressed hope for peace and security in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The countries of the region should strive to manage their own
affairs and attain full independence politically, economically and
culturally, Khatami stressed in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Kyrgyz president voiced his support for the business of a
joint economic commission between the two countries for the
improving trade and economic relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
