<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40 Cities Nominated by UN for Human Settlement Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Forty cities worldwide, including
three in China, were nominated here for the 2000 Dubai
International Award of Best Practices by the United Nations Center
for Human Settlement.
</P>
<P>
The three Chinese capital cities are Shenyang in Liaoning
province, Chengdu in Sichuan province, and Kunming in Yunnan
province.
</P>
<P>
An official from the center disclosed that the center selected
the 40 cities from 700 applications from 110 countries.
</P>
<P>
Information about the cities will be stored in the center's
database for reference, the official added.
</P>
<P>
All the three Chinese cities were chosen for their remarkable
achievements in improving the environment, he said, adding that
Shenyang was named for setting a good example for other industrial
cities in realizing sustained development in urban construction.
</P>
<P>
Kunming and Chengdu were nominated respectively for their
success in easing urban traffic and treating waste water, the U.N.
official noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that ten cities will be finally chosen from the 40
cities for the best human settlement award, and the finalists will
be announced at a ceremony in Dubai, the United Arab Emirates, in
October. Winners will be awarded 30,000 US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The award for human settlement, presented every two years, was
established by the center in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
