<HEADLINE> 19 Scientists Win Top Prizes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen Chinese scientists were
awarded Tan Kah-kee Science Prize and the China Engineering
Science and Technology Award here today.
</P>
<P>
The two prizes, highly esteemed by scholars of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the Chinese Academy of Engineering (
CAE), represent the highest honors available to Chinese scientists.
</P>
<P>
Eight scientists won Tan Kah-kee prizes in mathematics and
physics, chemistry, life science, agricultural science, medical
science, geology, information science and science of technology.
</P>
<P>
Another 11 scientists, all scholars with the Chinese Academy of
Engineering, won the China Engineering Science and Technology
awards.
</P>
<P>
The Tan Kah-kee Foundation was started in 1988, and presents
its prize every two years to award Chinese scientists in eight
scientific fields.
</P>
<P>
The China Engineering Science and Technology Award Foundation
began in 1996. Some 37 Chinese engineers, scientists and scholars
in engineering science and technology have won the award. 
</P>
</TEXT>
