<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNIFIL Carries out Task of Verifying Israeli Withdrawal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 9 (Xinhua) -- U.N. peacekeeping troops in south
Lebanon have begun the belated verification of Israel's withdrawal
from south Lebanon and the process will be finished by Friday.
</P>
<P>
Once the United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL) is
able to confirm that Israel has completed a troop withdrawal from
all of Lebanon, the peacekeeping force can proceed with its
expansion plans and begin deploying up to the border, Daily Star
newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
UNIFIL spokesman Timur Goksel confirmed two inspection teams,
accompanied by Lebanese and Israeli officers, began verifying the
withdrawal on both sides of the border early Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
They set out from the Lebanese border point at Ras Naqoura on
the Mediterranean Sea coast and from Rosh Hanikra on the Israeli
side, and reached as far as Ramiye, 22.5 kilometers inland by
evening, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The teams will check the line of withdrawal finalized by U.N.
cartographers earlier in the week up to the last UNIFIL position in
Lebanon on the edge of the Israeli-occupied Golan Heights near
Shebaa Farms. The Golan-based U.N. Disengagement Observer Force
(UNDOF) takes over peacekeeping duties beyond this point.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said "good progress had been made," but the team
on the Lebanese side of the border fences was being hampered by the
presence of land mines. The inspectors are being accompanied by a
UNIFIL mine clearance unit and an ambulance, LBC television
reported.
</P>
<P>
The length of the withdrawal line between Ras Naqoura and just
north of the Shebaa Farms is approximately 74 kilometers, 28 of
which runs between Lebanon and the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
However, it remained unclear whether a disagreement between the
U.N. and the Israelis over the placing of a border maker just south
of Misgav Am had been resolved before the UNIFIL teams set out from
the coast.
</P>
<P>
The Israelis had not contacted UNIFIL specifically over the
disputed hilltop location, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Al Nahar newspaper reported Friday the border fence
near the northern-most Israeli settlement of Misgav Am has been
pulled back 20 meters to tally with the line drawn by the United
Nations to confirm the authenticity of the withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
UNIFIL Commander Major General Seth Kofi Obeng will report to U.
N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on the outcome of the verification
operation in 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
Annan will then submit a report to the Security Council,
certifying that Israel withdraws completely to the internationally-
recognized borders in full compliance with U.N. Security Council
Resolution 425 of 1978.
</P>
<P>
Israel withdrew its forces from south Lebanon on May 24, ending
its 22-year occupation of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
