<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Picasso's Missing Painting Found in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A lost painting by world-famous
painter Pablo Picasso has been put in the State Painting and
Sculpture Museum in Ankara after it was retrieved in a police
operation in Izmir, western Turkey, earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The Fine Arts General Director Mehmet Ozel, who went to Izmir on
Culture Minister Istemihan Talay's order, brought the painting "La
Fermiere" to Ankara Thursday, reported Anatolia News Agency Friday.
</P>
<P>
A gang of six people was trying to sell the oil painting to
undercover police by chance for 6.5 million U.S. dollars before
they were arrested by the police.
</P>
<P>
The Head of the Izmir Police Fiscal Department, Serafettin
Bural, said they had been unable to find a home for the painting
after visiting all the museums in the Aegean port city.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters at a press conference that "La Fermiere" was
painted by Picasso, the pioneer of modern painting, in 1908 and
that there is the original signature of Picasso on the back of it.
</P>
<P>
Pablo Picasso (1881-1973), a Spanish painter, moved to settle in
Paris in 1904 and became a pioneer of the French modern painting.
He left behind thousands of works with the "Peace Dove" being one
of his most immortal masterpieces.
</P>
<P>
Ozel noted that in accordance with the registration on the back
of the painting, this art piece was displayed in France and in
Hermitage Museum in Moscow in 1930.
</P>
<P>
"La Fermiere" was reported to be seen for the last time in
Kuwaiti Emir's Palace. It was speculated that the painting was
stolen by an Iraqi officer during the Gulf War in 1991 and was
first taken to Iraq and at last to Turkey via Syria.
</P>
<P>
Ozel disclosed nobody has so far applied to Turkey regarding the
painting.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question whether it is safe to keep the painting in
the State Painting and Sculpture Museum, Ozel said the painting
will be put in a secure safe.
</P>
<P>
However, which country or whom the artifact belongs to has not
been determined yet.
</P>
<P>
"If a country or a person proves that it is the owner of the
painting, we will do what is necessary," said Culture Minister
Istemihan Talay in a message read out by Ozel.
</P>
<P>
However, whoever claiming to be the owner of the painting "
should prove this with documents which are accepted in
international platform."
</P>
<P>
The painting will be preserved under the guarantee of the
Culture Ministry until then, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysian Trades Union Launches Campaign for Minimum Wage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian Trades Union
Congress (MTUC) Friday launched a nationwide campaign to gather
support for its proposal of a monthly minimum wage of 900 ringgit
(236 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the campaign, members of the union will send postcards to
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad and Human Resources Minister Fong
Chan Onn, MTUC Secretary General G. Rajasekaran told a press
conference in Petaling Jaya near here.
</P>
<P>
"We estimate the minimum wage proposal will benefit at least 2
million workers in the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
The MTUC special committee on minimum wage has sought to have
the minimum wage at 900 ringgit a month, basing its calculations
on the essential and basic needs of a single person, he said.
</P>
<P>
A study of wage scales of 165 companies showed that even in
some major towns, unskilled workers were being paid as low as
between 300 ringgit (78 dollars) and 350 ringgit (92 dollars) per
month, he said.
</P>
<P>
The MTUC believes that if the minimum wage proposal is
implemented,thousands of women will return to work.
</P>
<P>
He said a minimum wage system must be put in place before
productivity-based annual wage increases can be implemented.
</P>
<P>
The MTUC also called for the establishment of a retrenchment
and unemployment fund, ratification and implementation of
International Labor Organization Convention 87 on Freedom of
Association and the Right to Organize, better maternity protection
and raising of the retirement age to 60.
</P>
<P>
He said these calls are contained in the postcards to be sent to
Mahathir and Fong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
