<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Prepares Slain Minister's Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
appointed a cabinet sub-committee to organize the funeral of the
slain Minister of Industrial Development C. V. Gunaratne,
officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Secretary to the president K. Balapatabendi said the government
will accord a state funeral to Gunaratne on Saturday at the People
's Park in the suburbs of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The minister was assassinated in a suicide bombing Wednesday
when he was leading a procession on the War Heroes Day to collect
donations for the army in his constituency in the southern suburb
of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The bombing was blamed on the separatist rebels of the
Liberation Tiger of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), who have plotted a string
of similar attacks in the capital since December as a part of
their 17-year campaign to carve out a homeland for minority Tamils
in Sri Lanka's north and east.
</P>
<P>
Balapatabendi said President Chandrika Kumaratunga was deeply
grieved by the death of one of her loyal and senior cabinet
ministers and had asked all other ministers to take necessary
precautions. 
</P>
