<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Some 20 kilograms of heroin,
worth about 200 million rupees (4.65 million U.S. dollars) in the
international market, was seized Thursday by officers of the Tamil
Nadu Narcotics Intelligence Bureau (NIB) from a lorry at Salem in
south India, an NIB press release said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Four persons -- one each from Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh
and two from Dindigu in Tamil Nadu -- have been taken into custody
in this connection, according to the Press Trust of India.
</P>
<P>
A police team intercepted the lorry on the Bangalore-Salem road
and seized 20 packets of the contraband concealed in a secret
chamber beneath the tool box.
</P>
<P>
The lorry earlier unloaded a consignment of steel pipes at
Hosur, police said. 
