<HEADLINE> Anhui Province Seeking Overseas Cooperation in Building Roads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province is
seeking overseas cooperation in road construction.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to build 8,000 km of roads in the coming
five years, 1,800 km of which are expressways. The projects are
estimated to cost 50 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, Anhui has used 200 million US dollars
of loans from The World Bank for local road construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
