<HEADLINE> China Initiates Project of Refueling with Banking Card </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- China Petro-Chemical Co. Ltd. (CPCC)
signed an agreement here today with the Bank of China and the
China Construction Bank (CCB) to build a banking card system,
especially for CPCC's filling stations.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the project said that the refueling card system
will draw on the two banks powerful settlement system and strong
financing capability to develop electronic retailing of oil
products and on-line settlement businesses. Card holders can
refuel and pay in different places and enjoy better, faster and
safer services.
</P>
<P>
The CPCC boasts China's largest oil products sales network and
market shares, with 15,000 gas stations in 19 provinces and
municipalities, selling more than 48 million tons of oil products
in 1999, valued at 120 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The CPCC is expected to sell more than 52 million tons of oil
products by the end of the year, accounting for half of the
domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Bank of China and the CCB said that both banks
will fully exploit their advantages in computer networks, services,
technologies and banking card businesses to provide financial
services and support for the project.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, the Bank of China and the CCB issued
various banking cards worth more than 20 million and 57.9 million,
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
