<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-Italy Workshop on Hydrogen Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The China-Italy Workshop on
Hydrogen, co-sponsored by China's Ministry of Science and
Technology, the Italian Embassy to China and the China Energy
Research Society, was held here today with many world-famous
energy experts attending.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Carlo Rubbia, chairman of the Italian National Board for
New Technology, Energy and Environment and laureate of Nobel
Physics Prize, and Shi Dinghuan, director of the Department of
High Technology and Industrialization under the Ministry of
Science and Technology, as well as other senior experts, delivered
keynote speeches.
</P>
<P>
Discussions and panels at the workshop included using hydrogen
to reduce pollution, an overview of hydrogen energy in China,
hydrogen from coal with zero emission, and production and
utilization of hydrogen in China.
</P>
<P>
Shi Dinghuan briefed the attendants on hydrogen energy
developments in China, saying that China has make remarkable
progress in hydrogen production, storage and utilization.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that the Chinese government has encouraged the
development of various new and renewable energy sources including
hydrogen energy. China has a number of well-known hydrogen
research experts from colleges and universities, the Chinese
Academy of Sciences, and petroleum and petrochemical sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said that more regular international exchanges of this kind
are welcomed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
