<HEADLINE> United Airlines Opens Beijing-San Francisco Non-Stop Daily Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- United Airlines has become the
first airline to open a non-stop daily flight between Beijing and
San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
The new flight will meet the increasing demand of passengers
traveling between the United States and China. said Christopher
Lin, the Airlines' general manager in China, at the opening
ceremony held at Beijing Capital International Airport.
</P>
<P>
"Passengers will able to transfer to any place in the U.S from
San Francisco with our efficient service facilities there," said
Lin.
</P>
<P>
The non-stop flight UA802 leaves Beijing at 16:30 every
afternoon and arrives in San Francisco at 12:55 (American Time)
the same day.
</P>
<P>
United opened a non-stop flight between Shanghai and San
Francisco on April 3. 
</P>
