<HEADLINE> Librarians Call For Chinese Resources Database System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A group of Chinese and foreign
librarians attending an international conference here have called
for the establishment of a database system to disseminate Chinese
language resources.
</P>
<P>
English-language information dominates the Internet, while
Chinese-language information makes up less than one percent of the
world's total.
</P>
<P>
The different coding systems adopted by China's mainland, Hong
Kong and Taiwan add to the difficulties in the sharing of Chinese-
language information, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
The three day conference which closed today decided to set up a
Chinese METADATA workshop to provide a uniform Chinese-language
database.
</P>
<P>
Some 62 librarians from the mainland, the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), Macao SAR, Taiwan, and the United
States and the Netherlands attended the conference.
</P>
<P>
The annual conference will be held in Taipei next year.
</P>
