<HEADLINE> Arafat in Cairo for Discussions of Mideast Peace Process 1st Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
arrived in Cairo Friday on a short visit for discussions with
Egyptian leaders on the latest developments of the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after his arrival, Arafat headed to a meeting with
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders were joined by their senior aides, including
Arafat's deputy Mahmoud Abbas and Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, the two leaders are expected to
review the results of the Mideast tour by U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright and her talks with both of them.
</P>
<P>
They will discuss ways of pushing forward the Palestinian-
Israeli peace talks, which Palestinian Ambassador in Cairo Zohdi
al-Qedra said are faltering because of Israeli evasive tactics.
</P>
<P>
Albright visited Israel and the Palestinian self-rule areas on
Monday and Tuesday, and came to Cairo on Wednesday. The
Palestinians and Israel have agreed to resume their final-status
negotiations near Washington next week for a final peace agreement
for which the two sides imposed a September 13 deadline to be
reached.
</P>
<P>
Arafat frequently visits Egypt to consult and coordinate with
Mubarak on the peace process and seek his advice. 
</P>
