<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host Int'l Conference on Plant Genetic Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 9 (Xinhua) -- An International Conference on
Science and Technology for Managing Plant Genetic Diversity in the
21st Century will be held in Malaysia from June 12 to 16 to
examine the current state of genetic resources conservation.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 experts in genetic resources and policy makers from
around the world will attend the conference here to forge a plan
to meet food needs in the 21st century, the International Plant
Genetic Resources Institute (IPGRI) said in a statement here.
</P>
<P>
Plant genetic resources determine the characteristics of plants,
including their ability to adapt and survive and the use of these
resources can ensure food security and drive the economic and
social development of the world's growing population, said the
institute, which has its regional office for Asia, the Pacific and
Oceania based here.
</P>
<P>
The conference is co-hosted by the Malaysian Palm Oil Board and
the Rome-based IPGRI, the world's largest international institute
dedicated to the conservation and use of plant genetic resources
with the support of the Ministry of Science, Technology and
Environment and the Malaysian government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
