<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Spokesman of the Indonesian
Military(TNI) Vice Marshal Graito Usodo confirmed here Friday that
there will soon be a reshuffle in the military, but he declined to
elaborate on the changes.
</P>
<P>
"There will be a tour of duty soon," Usodo was quoted by Antara
news agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
"(But) only after the issuance of a letter of decision can I as
TNI spokesman, announce (the decision) to the public," he added.
</P>
<P>
There have been rumors of the reshuffle of several officers
after the recent resignation of acting State Secretary Bondan
Gunawan.
</P>
<P>
It was rumored that the impending reshuffle might cover the
post of TNI commander, which is rotated among TNI's three pillars--
the army, the navy, and the air force.
</P>
<P>
The present TNI commander is Adm. Widodo A.S. from the navy.
</P>
<P>
"The post of commander of the Army Strategic Reserve Command,
now occupied by Lt. Gen. Agus Wirahadikusumah, will reportedly
also be included in the tour of duty," Antara said.
</P>
<P>
But Usodo refused to make any straight comment on the matter.
</P>
<P>
"I should say there has been no confirmed information about the
personnel to be involved in the coming tour of duty," Usodo said.
</P>
