<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Friday on a technical rebound
after registering losses over the past six trading days.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100 quality stocks Composite Index gained 19.
06 points to 861.3, the all-share Emas Index added 5.06 points to
216.79, the Industrial Index surged 40.82 points to 1,509.44 and
the Second Board Index rose 7.69 points to 226.67.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 686 to 56 while 77 counters were
unchanged and 159 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
