<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Calls for Speeding Up Zhongguancun Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing has
called for speeding up the development of the Zhongguancun high-
tech development zone in Beijing, known as China's "Silicon Valley.
"
</P>
<P>
During his inspection to the zone on Thursday, Li, also member
of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, said that the central
authorities have high hopes for the zone and that joint efforts
should be made to promote its development.
</P>
<P>
Located in Haidian District of Beijing, Zhongguancun boasts
more than 1,227 high-tech enterprises, producing 52.7 billion yuan
of industrial goods last year. It has become a leading force
behind Beijing's fast economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said that over the past year, Zhongguancun has
made a lot of progress with help from the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, Beijing University, Qinghua University and other
institutions of higher learning in the area.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed the hope that Zhongguancun will become a good
example for high-tech development zones in other parts of the
country. 
</P>
