<HEADLINE> Thailand Well-Prepared for ASEAN Meeting: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is well-prepared for the
upcoming 33rd meeting of foreign ministers of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and related forums, a senior
security officer said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Savek Vatanakij, commander of Special Branch Division 2 of Thai
Police, was quoted by the Thai News Agency as saying security
officers had been prepared to impose security measures and provide
safeguards to ASEAN leaders and their counterparts from key
countries in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN meetings are to be held here between July 21 and 29.
</P>
