<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
arrived in Cairo Friday on a short visit for discussion with
Egyptian leaders on the latest developments of the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is to meet with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak shortly
after his arrival, according to Egypt's Press Center.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will review the results of the Mideast tour by
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and her talks with both
of them, Palestinian Ambassador in Cairo Zohdi al-Qedra said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
