<HEADLINE> Philippine Autonomous Region Chief Denies Independence Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Governor Nur Misuari of the
Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao (ARMM) said Friday that he
has no intention of reviving the bid of the Moro National
Liberation Front (MILF) for independence.
</P>
<P>
Misuari said in a radio speech that President Joseph Estrada
continues to give his "generous support" to the development of the
autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
"Until now, the great majority of the leadership (of the MILF)
still would like to give government a chance to prove its
sincerity especially with President Estrada giving his generous
support for the bridge construction," Misuari said.
</P>
<P>
President Estrada has reportedly ordered concerned government
agencies to speed up the construction of these bridges, which will
link the four provinces of the autonomous region -- South Lanao,
Tawi-Tawi, Sulu and Maguindanao -- and spur development there.
</P>
<P>
On its part, the presidential palace expressed satisfaction
over Misuari's assurance that he is not seeking to revive his bid
for independence, but reminded him that he should account for the
funds received by his region from the national government.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora said Misuari, just like any
other government official, must make an accounting of public funds
under his supervision.
</P>
<P>
"What should be done by the Senate is to ask for the accounting
not only of the funds under Misuari but also of the funds under
other ARMM officials," Zamora said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
