<HEADLINE> Belgian PM Hopes Soccer not hooligans to Steal Limelight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BRUSSELS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Prime Minister Guy
Verhofstadt said he hoped football and not hooligans would steal
the limelight during the Euro 2000 soccer championship.
</P>
<P>
"I very much hope that in the next few weeks we will talk
about football and not hooligans," the Preme Minister told Reuters
in an interview.
</P>
<P>
Belgium, together with its lowlands neighbour the Netherlands,
is hosting the 16-nation tournament, which begins on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Both countries have been keen to show they are prepared to
deal with any possible violence among soccer fans and have fended
off suggestions their security arrangements were inadequate.
</P>
<P>
"The footballers are ready, everything is ready," Verhofstadt
was quoted as saying by Reuters.
</P>
<P>
Belgium will host the match between Germany versus England, in
Charleroi on June 17. Both sides' fans have a reputation for
violence and are fierce rivals, Reuters said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
