<HEADLINE> Chongqing-HK, Chongqing-Macao Economic Promotion Associations Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chongqing-Hong Kong
Association for Economic Promotion and the Chongqing-Macao
Association for Economic Promotion were established today.
</P>
<P>
He Guoqiang, secretary of the Chongqing Municipal Committee of
the Chinese Communist Party, said that the formation of the two
organizations shows that the economic, technological and cultural
cooperation between Chongqing and Hong Kong, and Chongqing and
Macao have reached a new stage of development.
</P>
<P>
Tam Pak Yuen, secretary for Economy and Finance of government
of the Macao Special Administrative Region, said at the
inauguration ceremony that there is a good basis for cooperation
between Macao and Chongqing because Macao is a bridge connecting
European countries, while Chongqing is a gateway to western China.
</P>
<P>
Howard Young, chairman of the Hong Kong Chamber for Textiles,
said that people from all walks of life in Hong Kong are highly
interested in the development of China's western regions,
especially Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
He said Chongqing provides excellent conditions for Hong Kong
businesspeople to participate in the development of western China.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's investments in the country's western regions
involve electronics, cement and tourism.  
</P>
