<HEADLINE> China to Open Second Board Early 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The adviser was quoted by today's "Shanghai Securities News" as
saying that the Chinese authorities have been actively pushing for
the establishment of a second board market.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, reforms in the stock issuance system has seen
the market playing a greater role in listings and improved
performances of listing companies, intermediaries and the
regulators.
</P>
<P>
Noeh told a symposium on listings in Urumqi, capital of
