<HEADLINE> China Unicom Has Ten Million Mobile Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The China Unicom, the second
largest mobile phone operator in China, has more than ten million
mobile phone users.
</P>
<P>
Opening mobile networks in four cities in 1995, the firm enjoys
nearly ten percent of mobile market shares.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom will have 15 to 18 million mobile phone users by
the end of the year. The figure is expected to reach 55 to 60
million by 2005.
</P>
<P>
The China Unicom's mobile phone network capacity is 14 million
and the figure will reach 30 million by the end of the year.
</P>
