<HEADLINE> Plush Hotel in Wellington Up for Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Parkroyal, the top hotel in
Wellington, capital city of New Zealand, is now for sale, The
Evening Post reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Parkroyal Wellington hotel is owned by AMP Office Trust. AMP is
one of the biggest insurance companies in New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The owner of the hotel, which is located in the heart of the
city's central business district, is to sell the business and
building, most likely to an overseas hotel chain and a sale tender
is to begin next week, according to the Wellington-based newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The 4.5-star hotel has 233 rooms, five conference venues, four
restaurants and bars, a gym, sauna and an indoor swimming pool. It
has a market value of about 26 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, Wellington does not have a true five-star hotel.
</P>
