<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Military, MILF Clash Anew in Mindanao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Intense fighting broke out anew on
Friday between the Philippine government forces and the Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) in central Mindanao, Philippine
News Agency(PNA) said.
</P>
<P>
The focus of the encounters is in the vicinity of the MILF
camps in Carmen and Pikit, all in North Cotabato Province, the PNA
noted.
</P>
<P>
Fighting is so intense that it spilled over to the Cotabato-
Davao highway in the area, prompting local authorities to close
down the route.
</P>
<P>
In Pikit, heavy fighting is going on in the villages of
Daungawin and Nalapaan where some 500 rebels are presently holed
up.
</P>
<P>
Aside from Carmen and Pikit, another affected town is Aleosan
where a civilian, Leopoldo Tomagos, was killed in crossfire and
three government soldiers were wounded in clashes that started
early Friday.
</P>
<P>
As of the report time, heavy exchanges of gunfire, punctuated
by mortar shelling, could be heard by stranded motorists along the
Cotabato-Davao route.
</P>
<P>
The Moro rebels are fighting for the creation of a separate
Islamic state in the Mindanao area. However, the military has
launched intensified attacks to frustrate MILF's secessionist bid.
</P>
</TEXT>
