<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Museveni Meets Carter Center Boss on Uganda-Sudan Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
discussed relations between his country and Sudan with Ben
Hoffman, director of the Conflict Resolution Programme of the
Carter Center, at State House in Kampala Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"They discussed issues related to Uganda-Sudan relations, the
implementation of the Nairobi accord signed by Museveni and Omar
Hassan Al- Bashir last December as well as other regional issues,"
Hope Kivengere, President's press secretary, told Xinhua Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hoffman, recently appointed by former U.S. President Jimmy
Carter, is on a fact-finding tour of the Great Lakes region. He
flew to Sudan to meet President Al-Bashir Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sources said Hoffman's tour is a follow-up of the
Museveni-Bashir Pact and a search for solutions to the fresh
clashes between Uganda and Rwanda in the war-torn Democratic
Republic of the Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
