<HEADLINE> Daily Report on Quality of Air in Key Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan, Shanghai,
Nanjing, Suzhou, Nantong, Wuhan, Guiyang, Lanzhou and Xining had
extremely slight air pollution today, according to a report issued
by the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Tianjin, Hohhot, Shenyang, Dalian, Changchun, Harbin,
Hangzhou, Wenzhou, Hefei, Fuzhou, Nanchang, Jinan, Qingdao, Yantai,
Zhengzhou, Zhanjiang, Chongqing, Chengdu, Kunming, Xi'an and
Urumqi enjoyed fairly good air.
</P>
<P>
Excellent air was reported in Xiamen, Changsha, Guangzhou,
Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Shantou, Nanning, Haikou, Lhasa and Yinchuan.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Tianjin, Shenyang, Dalian, Harbin, Shanghai, Nanjing,
Suzhou, Hangzhou, Xi'an, and 19 other cities listed absorbable
suspended particles as the major pollutants, while sulfur dioxide
was the major pollutant in Guiyang, Kunming and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly
under the central government, the provincial and regional capitals
and 10 key coastal cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
