<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Sees More Abortions in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- More than 15,500 abortions were
performed in New Zealand during 1999, about 3.1 percent more than
in 1998,according to figures released by Statistics New Zealand
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The latest increase compares with a drop of 1.2 percent during
1998 and an annual average jump of 5.6 percent during the years
from 1993 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
The abortion rate (number of abortions per 1,000 women aged 15-
44 years) rose from 17.5 in 1998 to a new high of 18.2 in 1999.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's abortion rate is significantly higher than that
for the Netherlands, Germany and Finland, all with a rate below 11
per 1,000,but is lower than that of Australia and the United
States, both of which have a rate of above 22 per 1,000.
</P>
<P>
The age group of 20-24 years remains the most common age for
abortions in New Zealand, accounting for approximately three out
of 10 abortions in any year. These women had the highest abortion
rate of 34.8 per 1,000 in 1999, followed by those aged 25-29 years
with an abortion rate of 24.5 per 1,000 and women aged 15-19 with
an abortion rate of 21.7 per 1,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
