<HEADLINE> 10 Nepalis Killed in Guerrilla-Police Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some 1600 guerrillas members opened fire at a police post in a
village in Jajarkot district and managed to capture the post after
the police ran out of their munitions, the Radio Nepal said.
</P>
<P>
At least 8 police and 2 guerrillas were killed in the cross-
fire while 36 injured police managed to flee to the district
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The fate of the rest of the police in the post is still unclear,
the injured police were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a six-member police sent as a reinforcement to the
besieged police post managed to escape an ambush by the guerrillas
and were forced to disband and retreat, said the Radio Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Over 1300 people, including police, guerrillas and civilians,
have been killed in guerrillas related clashes since the
guerrillas began armed activities in 1996. 
</P>
