<HEADLINE> Croatia, Romania Support Clearing Danube River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 8, (Xinhua) -- Visiting Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu and his Croatian counterpart Stjepan Mesic Thursday
pledged support for clearing the Danube River and building oil
pipelines linking the Caspian, Black and Adriatic seas.
</P>
<P>
Mesic said after the meeting of the two leaders that his
country is interested in clearing the Danube as it will lead to
the re-opening of its Vukovar port and boost the economic
development of that area, the Croatia radio and television station
reported.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that two countries will make efforts to
build petroleum pipelines linking the three seas and that a
Romanian experts delegation would soon head for Zagreb to discuss
the matter further.
</P>
<P>
During NATO's airstrikes against Yugoslavia last year several
bridges over the Danube were destroyed, which has blocked the
waterway and caused heavy economic loss to the countries along the
river.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian president arrived here Thursday for a state visit.
