<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Myanmar Win in Asian Youth Soccer Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian youth team beat the
Lao team 2-1 in the first match of the 9th Asian Youth Under-16
Soccer Qualifiers Group-9 which began here Thursday, official
newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar youth team defeated the Guam elevent 26-0 in the
second match of the qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
The youth soccer teams from Myanmar, Malaysia, Guam and Laos
are taking part in the group competition.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the matches will continue here on Saturday and next
Monday. 
</P>
