<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Western China Reports Fast Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Western China has witnessed rapid
economic development in the first four months of this year thanks
to the implementation of the strategy for developing the vast
western region.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that during the January-April period, six of
the ten provinces, a municipality and autonomous regions including
Guizhou, Chongqing, Shaanxi, Ningxia, Sichuan and Tibet all
reported an increase of over 10 percent in their total industrial
output values.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Province put an end to the loss-making situation of its
State-owned industrial enterprises, which lasted for six
consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
In fixed assets investment, Ningxia and Gansu scored an
increase of over 50 percent, respectively, Chongqing and Xinjiang
more than 30 percent, and Qinghai and Tibet, over 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
All these excluding Yunnan in the western region witnessed a 10
percent rise in retail sales in the first four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Guizhou is the only province in the western region which
suffered from the decrease of foreign trade in the four-month
period. Chongqing, however, had a 98.6 percent increase, and the
increase rate for Xinjiang and Tibet exceeded 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
The ten areas in western China cover a total area of 5.4
million square kilometers with a population of 300 million. The
region is rich in cultural and natural resources, and boasts
abundant mineral and energy resources.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government launched a campaign to develop its vast
western region late last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
