<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chengdu Wins Four Int'l Awards For Fine Environmental Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Chengdu, capital of southwest China
's Sichuan Province, has won four international awards for an
environmental project it has launched in its urban area.
</P>
<P>
All the four awards go to the comprehensive harnessing of the
Funan River which runs through downtown Chengdu. The project was
completed in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The latest award for the project is the "Local Initiative Award
" issued by the International Council for Local Environmental
Initiatives.
</P>
<P>
Chengdu invested heavily to tackle the Funan River in 1993, and
within five years, the city reinforced 16 km of the river course
and relocated 100,000 people to new residential areas.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the city also stopped all the 600 pipelines
which discharged waste water into the river, built 320,000
hectares of grassland, a flowing water park, a musical square and
other facilities.
</P>
<P>
The project won three medals in 1998 including one from the U.N.
Center for Human Settlement, one for its flowing water park from
an international organization, and a design award from the
International Environmental Design Research Association.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Development Program and the U.N. Center for Human
Settlement have regarded the project as a good example for big
cities in the world to follow.
</P>
<P>
The Funan River has been a city moat for Chengdu for 2,200
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Sector Turns Profitable in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The State-owned and State holding
enterprises in north China's port city of Tianjin have turned
losses into profit for the first time in the past three years,
posting a quarterly profit of 301 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The rosy picture in the State sector is closely related with
the recovering national economy and also attributable to the
municipal government's effort to restructure its economy and
introduce new technologies, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin pledged to eliminate deficit in the State sector by the
end of this year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 20 municipalities, provinces, and autonomous regions
in China reported profits in the State sector at the end of last
year. Tianjin was the only one in the eastern region to still have
loss-making State enterprises at the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has since intensified its effort to pull the
State sector out of difficulties, injecting 27 billion yuan into
the State-owned large or medium-sized enterprises to help them
upgrade technology.
</P>
<P>
The index measuring the economic efficiency of industrial
enterprises in Tianjin increased by 16.67 percent during the first
three months this year. Output of the State-owned industry
registered a rise of 14.7 percent during the period, the highest
increase into the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Large and medium-sized enterprises played a pivotal role in the
basic turnaround in the State sector. The profitable ones of these
enterprises, for instance, made 1.122 billion yuan of profit
during the January-March period, a surge of 64.5 percent from the
same 1999 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
