<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aid Continues to Arrive in Quake-Hit Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Social workers and medical teams both from Jakarta and many
foreign countries have started work to provide food and medical
aid to the injured.
</P>
<P>
Shushaki Hirayasu, who leads the Japanese medical team, was
quoted as saying that his team was concentrating on helping treat
hundreds of seriously injured victims in Muhammad Yunus General
Hospital in Bengkulu city, about some 540 kilometers northwest of
Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Emergency aid also reached remote Enggano island which lies
close to Sunday's earthquake's center. One Indonesian and two
Dutch naval ships anchored off the island, using helicopters to
bring in boxes of rice, noodles, tents and medicine.
</P>
<P>
However, relief efforts have been hampered by heavy rain,
damaged roads and severed communications.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that hundreds of people in the provincial
capital of Bengkulu on Thursday expressed frustration over what
they saw as the slow pace of emergency assistance to thousands of
people badly needing help.
</P>
<P>
They demanded faster supply of emergency aid and complained
that the government was neglecting them while foreign aid was
pouring into the quake zone.
</P>
<P>
At least 120 persons were killed and 2,300 others injured in
the strong earthquake measuring on 7.9 on the Richter Scale on
Sunday night. The epicenter of the quake was in the Indian Ocean
about 112 kilometers southwest of the western coast of Bengkulu.
</P>
<P>
A powerful aftershock measuring 6.2 on the Richter Scale jolted
this area again on Thursday morning. The Meteorological and
Geophysics Office said the aftershock's epicenter was near Enggano
island, some 120 kilometers from Bengkulu city, and 100 kilometers
below sea level.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of small aftershocks have followed the Sunday's
earthquake. Indonesian seismologists said the aftershocks would
continue through the week and expected to vanish only in two or
three weeks' time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
