<HEADLINE> Poland Names New Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Polish Prime Minister Jerzy Buzek
Thursday appointed Economy Minister Janusz Steinhoff as Deputy
Prime Minister; he also named three other officials from the
Solidary Election Action (AWS) as new ministers.
</P>
<P>
The appointment came after Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski's announcement on the same day to remove the Freedom
Union (UW) leader Leszek Balcerowicz and three other UW ministers
from their positions.
</P>
<P>
Those newly-named ministers will replace their UW predecessors
who abandoned talks on saving the 30-month center-right ruling
coalition and announced their withdrawal from the cabinet last
week as finance minister, justice minister and transport and
maritime economic minister.
</P>
<P>
Buzek said Defense Minister Janusz Onyszkiewicz and Foreign
Minister Bronislaw Geremek, who are also UW members, will
temporarily stay in their positions for emergency affairs but will
leave the cabinet by the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
Buzek on Tuesday accepted the UW's resignation from the
government and is struggling to form a minority government.
</P>
