<HEADLINE> Foreigners in Beijing Pay Taxes With Bank Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Foreigners residing in Beijing have
paid 530,000 yuan (about 63,300 U.S. dollars) in taxes in the last
five months.
</P>
<P>
In the past only two cards issued by the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) could be used to pay tax.
Foreigners can now use various bank cards issued by the Bank of
China, Agricultural Bank of China, Construction Bank of China,
Bank of Communications and ICBC.
</P>
<P>
These changes have helped increase Beijing's local revenue in
the first quarter to 7.85 billion yuan, or a 26.5 percent increase.
