<HEADLINE> Mysterious Interruption of Cell Phone Network Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Intermittent intruding signals that
interrupted a major CDMA cellular phone network in Beijing for
five days have disappeared.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily quoted officials of Motorola, the system
provider, as saying that the problem did not come from its mobile
communications equipment.
</P>
<P>
The problem has not reoccurred since it disappeared on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Motorola revealed in statement that the problem was from
external interference, and the company is still monitoring the
operation of the system with the network operator.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that more than 30 technicians and experts
are trying to determine the cause of the interruption.
</P>
<P>
From June 1 to 5, complaints about abnormal function of phones
flooded into Beijing Telecom Great Wall Co., the network operator,
from its 133 network mobile phone subscribers. 
</P>
