</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A Russian commander was gravely wounded Thursday in
Chechnya on Thursday as federal troops continued their strikes on
the rebels in the breakaway republic.
</P>
<P>
Police Colonel Valery Konovalov, deputy commander of the
western army grouping, sustained head wounds near a checkpoint on
the road linking Urus-Martan and Gekhi road when the car he was
riding came under fire. His driver was killed, the Interfax news
agency reported. (Russia-Chechnya-Commander)
</P>
