<HEADLINE> Parke Beats Barada in Super Series Squash Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Simon Parke, the Englishman who
recovered from cancer three years ago, overwhelmed Ahmed Barada,
the Egyptian playing his comeback tournament after being knifed by
a stranger three months ago, to reach the final of the Super
Series squash Finals here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Parke defeated Barada 15-6, 15-6, 15-9. He will meet the
Scotsman Peter Nicol, the World Open champion, in the final.
</P>
