<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fair Play Earns Three Clubs UEFA Cup Berths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Norrkoping, Belgium's
Lierse SK and Spain's Rayo Vallecano have been granted spots in
next season's UEFA Cup after qualifying through the fair play
rankings, UEFA announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sweden finished top of UEFA's fair play ranking for the 1999-
2000 season which is based on a country's record in club and
national team competitions at all age levels.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish and Belgian clubs were drawn out of a hat from
among the other countries who finished in the top 15 of the
rankings.
</P>
<P>
National football federations nominated clubs by their own
criteria. The three teams will compete in the qualifying round of
the UEFA Cup in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
