<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamilton Wins Fourth Stage in Dauphine-Libere Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Tyler Hamilton became the second
successive American to win the Mont Ventoux stage of the Criterium
du Dauphine-Libere cycling race on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hamilton, who rides for Tour de France champion Lance Armstrong
's US Postal team, won the fourth leg -- a 159 kilometers run from
Romans to Mont Ventouz by four seconds. He clocked four hours 21
minutes and 26 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Alex Zuelle came in second with four seconds
behind, followed by Kurt Van de Wouwer of Belgium and American
Jonathan Vaughters was third.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Vaughters took the time trial on the tough mountain
course in Provence.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Haimar Zubeldia took the overall lead with a total
time of 14 hours 57 minutes and 22 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Hamilton finished second with three seconds behind and Lance
Armstrong of the United States dropped to third, 51 seconds behind
Zubeldia after a 20-second penalty for illegal feeding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
