<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Siamese Twins Survive Surgical Separation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese doctors have successfully
separated two Siamese twins who were joined at the chest, abdomen
and liver in Puyang city of central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The twin infant boys weighed only 2,500 kilograms before the
surgery. Doctors said the survival rate for such light Siamese
twins is very low after separation.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the success of the surgery, medical experts were
pooled in the hospital to work out the best way to separate the
twins. The surgery lasted more than three hours and the twins are
currently recovering well under special-care treatment in the
hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
