<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0289 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shearer Faces Anxious Wait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- England team captain Alan Shearer
has given England a major injury scare just four days ahead of
their opening match in the European Championship finals.
</P>
<P>
Shearer, who is the cornerstone of Kevin Keegan's plans and has
started every single one of his 13 games in charge, underwent a
scan on a knee problem before flying out to the squad's base in
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Both Shearer and Keegan were expressing confidence the striker
would be able to face Portugal on Monday, although they were not
anticipating receiving the results of the "precautionary" scan
until at least Friday.
</P>
<P>
And while Shearer may not be able to train until Saturday, the
England coach - who revealed that a total of eight players have
undergone scans in the past week or so - will give him until the
last possible moment to prove his fitness.
</P>
<P>
Until the scan results come back without any problems, the news
therefore remains a major worry for England fans so close to the
start of the tournament, given that - for all his critics -
Shearer is the one regularly proven goalscorer at international
level within the squad.
</P>
<P>
However, he apparently went into last Saturday's game against
Malta with a "slight niggle" in his knee and then had to be
substituted after just 51 minutes after falling "awkwardly" during
the match.
</P>
<P>
Keegan had insisted earlier that Shearer was "fine" and would
train, yet he still felt the scan was necessary to get a
specialist view on the problem.
</P>
<P>
Just before boarding the flight to Belgium, Shearer revealed: "
I had a scan this morning just as a precaution to see if there's
anything in there.
</P>
<P>
"We'll wait for the results and take it from there. I don't
think it will be a problem," he said.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Newcastle forward, who is due to retire from
international football after the tournament, told Sky Sports.com:
"I think it needs another day or two to settle down. I'm very
confident, and the medical staff are very confident, that I'll be
back in training on Saturday."
</P>
<P>
Keegan, who only last week declared his confidence in his
players telling him the truth about the full extent of any injury
problems, added: "The scan is a precaution." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000609.0290 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aston Villa Vows to Fight to Keep Southgate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
Aston Villa will fight to the last to keep Gareth Southgate at the
club.
</P>
<P>
Southgate stunned the Villa Park hierarchy by slapping in a
transfer request just hours before he was set to depart on England
's Euro 2000 bid.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old central defender, who skippered Villa in their
FA Cup final defeat by Chelsea at Wembley last month, is unhappy
at the lack of ambition shown by his club and is looking for the
chance to express himself on the highest European stage.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United, Chelsea and Arsenal will have all been
alerted by Southgate's statement, which follows on closely from
the decisions of Ugo Ehiogu and Julian Joachim to leave the club
and Paul Merson's assertion that he will not be around at the
start of next season.
</P>
<P>
With manager John Gregory away on holiday as the continuing
turmoil envelopes his team, talks with Southgate will not take
place until England return from the tournament in Holland and
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
However, Villa chairman Doug Ellis has privately indicated that
he wants to keep one of his most influential players, even though
Gregory has previously said that he will not keep men whose
commitment can be called into question.
</P>
<P>
"Gareth Southgate is contracted to Aston Villa Football Club
for a further period of three years and remains an Aston Villa
player for this period," said the club in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"Gareth and the manager are out of the country at present and
the manager will be discussing the matter with Gareth at the
earliest possible opportunity." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
