<HEADLINE> Russian PM Vows to Keep Positive Economic Trends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Mikhail
Kasyanov on Friday pledged to build up current positive trends in
national economic development, which he described as "quite good."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the TV station ORT, he identified the
positive trends over the first five months of this year as stable
macroeconomic situation, controllable inflation, stable ruble
exchange rate and revenues ahead of budget targets, which made the
Central Bank's foreign currency reserve reach 20 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
What makes the premier optimistic about the prospects for the
current fiscal year includes that foreign investors are eager to
directly invest in Russia.
</P>
<P>
