<HEADLINE> German-Franco Consultation in Mainz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 BERLIN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
arrived in Mainz, the capital of the state of Rhineland-Pfalz, to
talk with German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder. It is the 75th
German-Franco Consultation.
</P>
<P>
The German-Franco consultation is a traditional summit of the
leaders in the post-war era. This time French Premier Lionel
Jospin also attended as well as the foreign and defense ministers
of both sides.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting Schroeder and Chirac made an announcement in
which two leaders stressed both countries were in full agreement
on the European Union's reforms and Balkan policy.
</P>
<P>
"We achieved far-reaching results both for our nations and
also for Europe," said Schroeder.
</P>
<P>
Chirac thought that the summit had shown the Franco-German
motor was running on full power.
</P>
<P>
German and French leaders reached an agreement on going ahead
with the Airbus A400M military airlifter. Germany will order 75
A400M airlifters and France will also purchase about 50 pieces.
</P>
<P>
Germany and France also announced in a declaration that they
would create a German-Franco spy satellite alliance which would be
open to other European states.
</P>
<P>
The German-Franco bilateral relations played an important role
as an axis of the European Union in the past. France will take
over the EU. rotating presidency for the second half of this year.
In December the EU summit will be held in the French city of Nice.
The reforms must be undergone before any new member states from
Eastern Europe can be admitted to the EU.
</P>
<P>
Chirac stressed that France would consider Germany's size with
regard to the weighting of votes in the European Council. Germany
has a population of 82 million and France has 59 million. But both
France and Germany have 10 votes in the Council.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder and Chirac had also discussed in their meeting about
the U.S.'s National Missile Defense system and the EU's sanctions
policy to Austria.
</P>
<P>
"We have the same view on the terrible consequences that NMD
could have ...," said Chirac. He was worried that the NMD system
would damage the Anti-Ballistic Missile (ABM) Treaty which was
signed in 1972 and strictly limited such missile defense system.
</P>
<P>
Chirac expressed that the NMD system will be a top issue at
the EU's summit in Nice.
</P>
<P>
About the question whether they had discussed possible lifting
the sanctions against Austria Schroeder said : "We see no reason
to introduce any changes."
</P>
<P>
France backed firmly to continue the embargo on Austria.
Because the rightist Freedom Party (FPOe) led by Joerg Haider
joined the Austrian Government last February 14 EU. states decided
to boycott it as a reaction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
