<HEADLINE> 4 European Countries to Produce 366 New Military Helicopters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first group of orders for the helicopters, which are
capable of carrying about 20 soldiers each, will be made in the
next few weeks from the four countries, said sources close to the
deal which was signed on Thursday in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Germany will buy 134 NH 90 helicopters, Italy 117, France 95
and the Netherlands 20, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The helicopters will be made jointly by the French-German
Eurocopter, the Italian Agusta, and the Dutch Fokker and their
first examples will come out of assembly lines by 2003, eight
years after the project was launched to rival the U.S. S92
helicopter.
</P>
<P>
Apart from those to be ordered by the four countries, from 500
to 600 more such helicopters are expected to be produced in the
next 20 years for export, said officials at Eurocopter.
</P>
<P>
The Scandinavian countries could buy from 70 to 90 such
helicopters in an on-going bidding, while Britain, Spain, Portugal,
Greece and Singapore have also expressed their interest. 
</P>
