<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Launches Counter-Offensive Against Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia Friday said that its
troops have launched a counter-offensive against Eritrean forces
at the eastern frontier and inflicted heavy losses on them.
</P>
<P>
The counter-offensive, which began last night, was in response
to repeated Eritrean provocations at the Bure front, the Office of
the Ethiopian Government Spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the operation was very successful, the office said
Ethiopian troops continued their counter-offensive up to Friday
evening.
</P>
<P>
According to the office, Eritrean army also provoked Ethiopian
positions at the central Senefe front Friday morning in the
vicinity of the Imbaseira Mountain, but the Eritrean attack was
effectively repulsed.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the western front, the office said the Eritrean
troops incited hostilities in the vicinity of Guluj, resulting in
small-scale fighting.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrea, which have been at war since May 1998 due
to border disputes, had a new round of large-scale border conflict
between May 12 and 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the sustained mediation by the Organization of
African Unity (OAU), representatives of the two countries have
been in indirect peace talks in Algiers, Algeria, since the
beginning of June under the auspice of OAU Chairman, Algerian
President Abdelaziz Bouteflika. 
</P>
