<HEADLINE> Bolivian Economy Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Bolivian economy grew 1.6 percent
in the first quarter of 2000, Economic Development Minister Jose
Luis Lupo said Friday in the country's capital city of La Paz.
</P>
<P>
The Bolivian economy grew only 0.6 percent in 1999 due to the
influence of the turmoil on world financial markets, according to
reports reaching here from Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia is now seeing the beginnings of recovery thanks to
growing agricultural and livestock production, which together make
up some 19 percent of the nation's gross domestic product, Lupo
said.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that such sectors as mining and
manufacturing were also beginning to show signs of growth.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia's government has predicted that full-year economic
growth will total some 3.5 percent in 2000. 
</P>
